# REALISTIC-LOAN-APPROVAL-INSIGHT-VISUALISATION
##I am a data analytics student with a strong interest in transforming raw financial data into meaningful insights that support informed decision-making. Through practical projects, I apply analytical thinking, visualization tools, and storytelling techniques to solve real-world business problems‚Äîparticularly in finance and lending systems.
üéØ Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing loan approval patterns using realistic financial and demographic data. The goal is to identify the key factors that influence whether a loan application is approved or rejected, and to present these insights through clear, interactive visualizations.
The dashboard simulates how banks and financial institutions evaluate loan applications to minimize risk and improve approval accuracy.
üìÇ Dataset Description
The dataset used in this project includes the following variables:
Applicant ID
Loan Status (Approved / Rejected)
Annual Income
Credit Score
Loan Amount
Total Credit
Employment Duration (Years Employed)
Year
These variables reflect common criteria used in real-world loan approval systems.
üîç Key Analytical Questions Answered
What is the overall loan approval rate?
How does credit score affect loan approval decisions?
What is the relationship between annual income and loan approval?
Does a higher loan amount reduce approval chances?
How does employment duration influence approval outcomes?
What trends exist in loan approvals over time?
üìà Visualization & Dashboard Features
KPI Cards
Total Loan Applications
Total Approved Loans
Total Rejected Loans
Average Credit Score
Total Loan Amount
Interactive Charts
Approved vs Rejected Loans (Bar Chart)
Credit Score vs Loan Status (Column Chart)
Annual Income vs Approval Rate (Bar Chart)
Loan Amount Distribution (Histogram / Column Chart)
Yearly Loan Approval Trend (Line Chart)
Slicers for Interactivity
Loan Status
Year
Credit Score Range
These elements allow users to dynamically explore loan approval patterns.
üí° Key Insights Discovered
Applicants with higher credit scores have significantly higher approval rates.
Stable and higher annual income strongly increases loan approval probability.
Large loan amounts are more likely to be rejected when income or credit score is low.
Longer employment duration improves approval outcomes.
Loan approval trends vary across different years, indicating policy or market changes.
üõ† Tools & Technologies Used
Microsoft Power BI
Microsoft Excel (Pivot Tables & Charts)
Data Cleaning & Transformation
Data Visualization Techniques
üöÄ Conclusion
This project demonstrates how data visualization can provide realistic insights into loan approval decisions. By combining financial indicators with interactive dashboards, the analysis supports better risk assessment and decision-making in lending institutions.
